        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 8:14PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Zortman, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Zortman and Landusky.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
